thread.title: Strong miners lead market higher

title: Strong miners lead market higher
text:
Fri, Sep 4, 2015, 4:59 PM AEST - Australia Markets closed Strong miners lead market higher AAP â€“ 4 hours ago Print 
Mining and consumer stocks have steered the share market to higher ground after the ASX benchmark dipped below 5,000 points in early trade. 
BHP Billiton and Rio Tinto had bounded two per cent higher by noon AEST on the back of strengthening commodity values, but the banks remained flat after dragging on the market for most of the morning session. 
The info tech, utilities and telecoms sectors were also stronger, by about one per cent, with Telstra and Woolworths both up as well. 
KEY FACTS 
* At 1200 AEST on Friday, the benchmark S&P/ASX200 index was up 31.6 points, or 0.63 per cent, at 5,059.4 points. 
* The broader All Ordinaries index was up 30.3 points, or 0.6 per cent, at 5,079 points. 
* September share price index futures contract was 31 points higher at 5,036 points, with 21,754 contracts traded.
